	<tr>
	  <td width='100%' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2' align='center'>UNYIELDING WISH: THE JOURNEY</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	  <td width='100%'><font face='verdana' size='2pt'><html>

<head>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=windows-1252">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 4.0">
<meta name="ProgId" content="FrontPage.Editor.Document">
<title>New Page 1</title>
</head>

<body>

<p class="MsoNormal">~*Unyielding Wish: The Journey*~</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>Mallecus turned around.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>To
his shock and dismay, Alielle was still standing; he frowned.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>She was bleeding from several wounds where Mallecus's attack had
penetrated.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>She was holding her
right arm, applying pressure to one of the wounds; she looked a lot weaker now.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;I see I have underestimated your strength.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>That, or you got lucky.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Believe
me, I won't make that mistake again!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>I'asuka...&quot;
he began the same attack.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>Alielle stood and waited.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Then
she saw her opening.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>When he raised
the energy above his head, she leaped forward and ran straight for him.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>She slashed at him with her whip, raking him across the leg.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>The energy fizzled and disappeared as he hissed and brought his sword up
to block the attack from her right hand.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;You're not as dumb as you look,&quot; said Mallecus playfully as he
parried Alielle's attacks.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Several
blows were exchanged, some hitting their mark.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>Alielle slashed him across his shoulder, to which he returned a blow from
the hilt of his sword.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Alielle
stumbled backwards slightly, but regained her composure and advanced again.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>She lashed out with her whip only to have it wrap uselessly around his
plated forearm.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>She rushed up to
pierce at him with her sharp claw.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>He
brought his sword across his chest and blocked her attack, then grabbed her by
the wrist.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Why do you want hurt people?<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Why
do you hate so much?<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Didn't anybody
ever love you?&quot;<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Alielle looked
up at Mallecus pleadingly, tears forming in her own eyes.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">&nbsp; </span>He looked slightly shocked and glanced away.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>He jumped back and lowered his sword, his face showed no emotion.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Don't presume to think you know anything about me or the way I
feel,&quot; his voice was cold as ice.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>&quot;I
haven't the time for these games, however.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>I must be going.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Do not let
your guard down, girl, for I will be back to finish this.&quot;<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>His image began to slowly fade out, along with his two companions.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Mallecus!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Wait!&quot;
cried Alielle.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>&quot;I...want...to,&quot;
he disappeared, &quot;...help...you.&quot;<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>She fell to her knees with her last words and looked at the place in
which he had been standing.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>She
stared for a moment, before she caught movement from the corner of her eye.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>She looked over and saw the young Druid whom she'd fought for coming over
toward her.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;A...Alielle, is it?&quot; questioned the girl warily.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>&quot;A...are you okay?&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>Alielle brushed off the pain she was in and looked at her and smiled
warmly.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>&quot;Yes, I'll be fine!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>I'm so happy I could help you!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>What's
your name?&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Loria.&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;I'm very happy to meet you, Loria!&quot;<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>Alielle began to rise to her feet, but couldn't seem to get her legs
under her.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>She stumbled back on to
the ground.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Oh, you're hurt!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Let
me help,&quot; Loria had concern in her voice.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>She clasped her hands by her chest, bowed her head and closed her eyes.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>She whispered a small incantation and blue light began swirling around
Alielle's body.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>As it swirled, the
pain faded and her lesser wounds were healed.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>She was still injured, however, as she had taken several hearty blows but
they had been lessened now by Loria's healing.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>Loria helped Alielle to her feet.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Alielle
walked over to her pack and packed her claws away, but kept her whip tied at her
waist.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>She knew that she could be
attacked at any time and wanted to be prepared.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">&nbsp; </span>She walked with Loria back to the path and they turned to
face each other.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Loria looked at
Alielle and then hugged her.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Thank you so much, Alielle!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>I
don't know what I would have done if you hadn't shown up!&quot;<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">&nbsp; </span>Tears formed at the corners of her eyes.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;I hate to think what would have happened if I hadn't shown up.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>I'm glad you're okay,&quot; Alielle was clearly relieved.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;I have to get back to Kelethin now, my parents are probably worried
sick!&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;I'm sure they love you very much.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>Please be careful on your way back!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>Do you want me to go with you?&quot; Alielle offered.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;No, I know the way.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Plus
I don't want to delay your journey any more,&quot; Loria smiled.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">&nbsp; </span>&quot;I wish you luck on your journey.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">&nbsp; </span>May Tunare watch over you.&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;And you, Loria!&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>They hugged and began walking in their respective directions.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">&nbsp; </span>Alielle continued on her way to the port in Butcherblock
Mountains.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>While still a little
battered, she felt good that she had already done something good for Antonica.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>She was already working on her assignment.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>Alielle smiled to herself and kept walking.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;----------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>The air was salty and the wind was blowing as the Siren's Bane pulled in
to the port of Freeport.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>The
gangplank was lowered and people began moving on and off the ship.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>Alielle stepped on to the dock and looked around.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>The city sprawled out before her.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>It
seemed much larger than her hometown of Kelethin.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>Everywhere she looked there were shops and booths and buildings and
people.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">&nbsp; </span>Boy, there were people!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>A man bumping in to her broke her trance.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Outta the way!&quot; he barked as he walked past.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>Alielle called after him, &quot;S...sorry, sir!&quot; but he was already
lost in the crowd.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>She put it
behind her and picked up her packs and walked to check in at the Port
Authority's office.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>After she was done with the Port Authority, she exited back in to the
bustling town.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>She wandered through
the twisting streets and alleys and got herself thoroughly lost very quickly.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>It was getting dark and she thought she'd better find a place to stay for
the night.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>The search for an inn
ensued, but luckily she came upon one in a matter of minutes.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>Entering, she walked to the front desk and promptly got a room.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Here's your room, Miss,&quot; said the Inn Keeper as she showed
Alielle to her room.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>&quot;If you
need anything, just call for me.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>My
name is Brena.&quot;<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Brena walked
down the hall, leaving Alielle alone.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>She
set her stuff down and crawled in to bed.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>It
wasn't comfortable, but it was better than the cot she'd been sleeping on for
the last week or more.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>It only took
about 5 minutes before Alielle was out cold.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;----------------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>The next morning came entirely too soon.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>The early morning sun streamed through the window and illuminated the
room.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Alielle usually loved
mornings, but the journey had just tired her out.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>She groggily pulled her armor on and picked up her pack.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">&nbsp; </span>It was time to get started.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Goodbye Brena,&quot; said Alielle and smiled at the young
innkeeper, &quot;I really enjoyed my stay!&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;I'm glad to hear that.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Come
back again sometime!&quot;<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>Alielle waved as she exited the inn.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>She stepped outside and took a deep breath.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>She closed her eyes and listened to the wind blow through the streets and
to the sound of many conversations.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>It
was definitely a lot different than home.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">&nbsp; </span>She looked around, unsure of where exactly she was in the
city and which way was out.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>She
glanced right, then left.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>After
some consideration she decided that she would go left and headed out.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>A good night's rest had not improved her sense of direction.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">&nbsp; </span>The sheer size and complexity of Freeport still had her
completely puzzled.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>She continued
wandering the alleyways and streets, occasionally stopping to ask directions
from people who seemed to know what they were doing.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;So it was that way again?&quot; she questioned and pointed to her
left.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Yes, just go that way, then turn right at the second street.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>You'll see the Hogcaller's inn.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Go
past that and take a left and you're as good as out.&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Thank you very much!&quot;<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>She
smiled again and walked away, hoping that this time she would find the West
gates.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>After more wandering, she
came upon a huge marble building with an attractive fountain in the courtyard.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>Decidedly lost yet again, she went in to ask for help.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>Once inside, she flagged down the first person she saw.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">&nbsp; </span>&quot;Hail, kind sir!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>I
was wondering if you could help me.&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>The man stopped and turned to her.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>&quot;Sure,
what do you need, little one?&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;I seem to be a little lost and I was wondering if you could help me
out of this crazy place!&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Oh, of course I can.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>If
you'll just give me a moment I have to put these books away,&quot; he nodded at
the large stack of books he was carrying.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Do you want me to help?&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Would you, dear?<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>That
would be great!&quot; He handed her the stack of books he was carrying,
&quot;Follow me.&quot;<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>She followed
after him trying to balance the books and keep her backpack on.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>&quot;By the way, what is your name?&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Alielle,&quot; she said around the books, &quot;My name is Alielle
Taallis.&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Well, Alielle, welcome to Freeport.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>I am Locarme Zennix, one of the keepers of the scrolls here in the Temple
of Marr.&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;So that's what this place is,&quot; Alielle looked around the
awe-inspiring temple.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>&quot;We
didn't have anything like this back in Kelethin!&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>Locarme chuckled, &quot;I don't imagine you would.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>It would be awfully hard to get all this stone up in to a tree!&quot;<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>Alielle continued following Locarme up several flights of stairs until
they came upon a stone door.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>He
pushed it open and they entered.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>He
instructed her to put the books down on the table as he sat down in a chair.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>Locarme was huffing and puffing from the ascent.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>He stood up again and closed his eyes, his lips barely moving as he
whispered a short incantation.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>An
aura surrounded him and he seemed to be refreshed.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Wow!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>What was
that?&quot; inquired Alielle.<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>He smiled at her, &quot;It's just a small spell I know.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>It refreshes me and makes me feel invigorated.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">&nbsp; </span>Would you like to learn it?&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;I'd love to learn that!&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Okay, then help me with a few more stacks of books and I will show
you.&quot;<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>So Alielle helped
Locarme with several more loads of books.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Up
and down the stairs she went; Locarme stayed at the ground level saying he was
&quot;preparing&quot; the stacks for when she returned.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>At long last, the task was complete and Alielle raced back down the
stairs so Locarme could teach her that spell.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Go ahead and have a seat, dear,&quot; he motioned to one of the
chairs, &quot;It will take me just a moment to find the right scroll.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>Ah!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Here it is!&quot;<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">&nbsp; </span>He pulled a small scroll from the cabinet he was searching in
and handed it to Alielle.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;What do I do with this?&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Well, read it...scribe it.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Just
do whatever until you have it memorized.&quot;<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>Alielle opened the scroll and brought out her notebook.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>She began studying the scroll and making notations in her book.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>Time passed and she felt she had it all memorized.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;I'm done, Locarme, I'm done!&quot; Alielle jumped up from the table
and ran over to Locarme who was arranging some scrolls in another cabinet.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;That's great!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Now
let's see if you can cast it.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Go
ahead and concentrate and say the words.&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>Alielle closed her eyes and spoke the words, the aura surrounded her and
energy zinged about her body.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>She
finished and opened her eyes then proceeded to jump around excitedly that it had
worked.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>&quot;I did it, I did
it!&quot; she cried.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;My you're a fast learner,&quot; commented Locarme, Alielle
continued bouncing around in utter glee, &quot;and...energetic.&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>Alielle stopped bouncing and stood before Locarme.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>She bowed and thanked him for his teachings.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">&nbsp; </span>&quot;Now, how do I get out of here?&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Right...getting out of here.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>The
easiest way would be to just follow the wall on the right.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>If you follow that wall it will lead you out of the gates and you'll be
well on your way in no time!&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Oh thank you again, Locarme!&quot; she grabbed him and hugged him.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>He laughed and patted her shoulder.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Now, off with you before it gets dark out.&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>Alielle exited the Temple and followed Locarme's instructions.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>Eventually she saw the West gates and stopped at one of the shops there
to make sure she had enough supplies.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>As
she waved goodbye to the merchant she saw a dark shape near the wall.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>With blinding speed the figure rushed out and snatched some wares off of
the merchant's table.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Stop, thief!&quot; cried the shopkeeper.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>Alielle saw the figure running out the gates, she began to pursue.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>&quot;Stop!&quot; she called after it, &quot;I'm sure they won't do
anything if you just give it back!&quot;<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>The
figure did not stop though and it ran along the outer wall.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>Alielle was gaining on it and hoped she could pin it in the corner.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>Then, without warning, the figure seemed to disappear.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>It looked almost as if it had run THROUGH the wall.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>When she reached the corner, sure enough, the figure was not there.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>Alielle glanced about, looking up and down and left to right, hoping to
see where it had gone.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>After a
little searching, however, she could not find any trace of it.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>She sighed, &quot;Shucks, I wonder what was so important that it had to
be stolen.&quot;<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Alielle leaned
back on the wall to rest and nearly fell down as she passed right through it.</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>No sooner than she realized what had just happened, she also realized
that there was someone standing behind her.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;
</span>That someone didn't seem to be friendly either; she gathered that from
the dagger poking her in her lower back and the other one at her throat.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span style="mso-tab-count:1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>A man's voice spoke sounding rather menacing, &quot;Who are you and what
are you doing here?&quot;</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p>
</o:p>
</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;To Be Continued...</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;Next Chapter: Friend or Foe</p>
<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<o:p>
